        <h1>Performance of Countries In the Olympics</h1>
        <p>The Olympics occurs once every 4 years and it is an opporutnity for countries to compete in various sports for glory and recognition. Athletes spend years training
          for the opportunity to represent their country at the Olympics and it is always a spectacular event for people around the world. 
          This page offers an overview of every countries performance in both the Summer and Winter Olympics. 
          This visualisation shows the distribution of medals won across the world and the the number of medals won by each country compared to its population size.
        </p>
